// Figure 4.2: CQRS Request Lifecycle with MediatR
// Client → API → Validation → Handler → Repository → DB → Response

// ==================== ACTORS ====================
Client [icon: user, color: blue]
API Controller [icon: server, color: blue]
MediatR Pipeline [icon: cpu, color: green]
Validation Behaviour [icon: check-circle, color: orange]
Handler [icon: zap, color: green]
Repository [icon: database, color: purple]
Database [icon: hard-drive, color: red]

// ==================== COMMAND FLOW (Write) ====================
Client > API Controller : HTTP Request (POST/PUT/DELETE)
API Controller > MediatR Pipeline : Send(Command)
MediatR Pipeline > Validation Behaviour : Validate request
Validation Behaviour > Handler : If valid, continue
Handler > Repository : Execute business logic
Repository > Database : Persist changes
Database > Repository : Confirm
Repository > Handler : Return result
Handler > API Controller : Response
API Controller > Client : HTTP Response

// ==================== QUERY FLOW (Read) ====================
// Queries skip validation behaviour (no side effects)
// Client > API Controller : HTTP GET
// API Controller > MediatR Pipeline : Send(Query)
// MediatR Pipeline > Handler : Direct to handler
// Handler > Repository : Fetch data
// Repository > Database : SELECT
// Database > Handler : Return data
// Handler > API Controller : DTO Response

// ==================== KEY COMPONENTS ====================
// ValidationBehaviour: FluentValidation pipeline behavior
// Handler: IRequestHandler<TRequest, TResponse>
// Repository: IRepository interface from Core
